cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.SC, cs.CE, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category as it deals with comparing the performance and precision of Python tools for automatic differentiation in solving a mathematical optimization problem. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as automatic differentiation is a key technique used in training neural networks. The scientific computing (cs.SC) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with numerical computations. The computational engineering (cs.CE) sub-category is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing the geometrical structure of a cluster, which could have applications in materials science and engineering. Finally, the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with performance comparisons of different tools for automatic differentiation.
